steps.instruction:
### Prep
- Sliced the large red onions

### Steps
1. Cut onions into 1-inch slices. Combine molasses, soy sauce, brown sugar, rice vinegar, and chipotle powder; whisk until blended. Place 1/2 of the marinade in zip-top bag and reserve remaining 1/2 for later use
2. Add steaks and onions to zip-top bag; knead to coat, then let stand 20 minutes (or overnight) to marinate. 
3. Preheat grill (or grill pan) on medium. Remove steaks and onions from bag (discard marinade); sprinkle with salt
4. Grill 34 minutes on each side or until onions are tender and grill-marked and steaks are 125F (for medium rare; warm red center), 130F (for medium; warm pink center), or up to 170F (for well done)
5. Let steaks stand 3 minutes to rest.
6. Cut onions into bite-size pieces; toss with remaining 1/2 marinade. Slice steaks; serve topped with onions.

ingredients.note: Like ribeye ot New York Strip
